The kinetic energy of the ejected electron is  

\[
K = h\nu - \phi = \frac{hc}{\lambda}-\phi
\]

\[
\frac{hc}{\lambda}= \frac{(6.626\times10^{-34}\,\text{J·s})(3.00\times10^{8}\,\text{m·s}^{-1})}{100\times10^{-9}\,\text{m}}
           = 1.99\times10^{-18}\,\text{J}= 12.4\;\text{eV}
\]

\[
K = 12.4\;\text{eV} - 12.0\;\text{eV}=0.4\;\text{eV}=0.4(1.602\times10^{-19}\,\text{J})
   =6.4\times10^{-20}\,\text{J}
\]

Using \(K=\tfrac12 mv^{2}\) with the electron mass \(m=9.11\times10^{-31}\,\text{kg}\),

\[
v = \sqrt{\frac{2K}{m}} =\sqrt{\frac{2(6.4\times10^{-20}\,\text{J})}{9.11\times10^{-31}\,\text{kg}}}
   \approx 3.7\times10^{5}\ \text{m s}^{-1}
\]

